107. **Decision:** He hands it over—“It’s for you.”  
108. **Climax:** The man reads it—then vanishes;  
109. **Outcome:** The letter is gone—but Tariq now hears the man’s voice in the wind;  
110. **Clever Twist:** He wasn’t delivering the letter—he was the one who wrote it;  
111. **Worldbuilding Feature:** In this city, the dead can still speak—but only through letters;  
112. **Scene:** Tariq hands the letter. The man smiles. The world turns gray.

